verbs.description: infeoff (third-person singular simple present infeoffs, present participle infeoffing, simple past and past participle infeoffed or infeft)

examples: [...] while a minor he received a dispensation and special license from the king, dated 8 Jan. 1608, upon which by a precept from chancery he was infeft in all the lands possessed by his father on 26, 27, 28 and 29 April.
